339
00:33:52,093 --> 00:33:53,003
J.D. !

340
00:33:53,413 --> 00:33:54,687
Oh, my God!

341
00:33:56,813 --> 00:33:58,690
Now will you listen to me?

342
00:34:04,693 --> 00:34:05,887
Hold tight!

343
00:34:07,893 --> 00:34:09,042
Sorry.

344
00:34:10,173 --> 00:34:11,083
Stop!

345
00:34:11,813 --> 00:34:12,609
Hang on!

346
00:34:19,973 --> 00:34:21,167
Watch out!

347
00:35:22,053 --> 00:35:25,045
Ladies and gentlemen,
we are going to put a stop to it. . .

348
00:35:25,333 --> 00:35:28,086
. . .and we're going to start right here!

349
00:35:31,933 --> 00:35:34,083
We are going to put an end. . .

350
00:35:34,333 --> 00:35:39,088
. . .to violence in this state.
And you can take that to the bank!

351
00:35:43,453 --> 00:35:46,172
Hulland, plaster Storm's ass
with slime in the press.

352
00:35:46,453 --> 00:35:50,287
Make him responsible for that
hospital mess. Tail people he knows.

353
00:35:50,493 --> 00:35:52,085
We know how to do our job.

354
00:35:52,413 --> 00:35:55,928
Then show me. I'm starring in the
son of a bitch's home movies.

355
00:35:56,133 --> 00:35:59,364
If that crap gets out,
I'm looking at 30 years.

356
00:36:49,093 --> 00:36:50,765
Geraldo.

357
00:36:51,573 --> 00:36:53,006
Who's this guy?

358
00:36:53,213 --> 00:36:56,967
Our program came to an
unexpectedly violent conclusion.

359
00:37:14,453 --> 00:37:16,569
Are you crazy?
I can't come in to work.

360
00:37:16,813 --> 00:37:19,566
I can't even go
to my apartment, Martha.

361
00:37:19,813 --> 00:37:21,531
People are dead.

362
00:37:21,853 --> 00:37:22,968
Then where are you?

363
00:37:23,173 --> 00:37:26,245
I can't tell you. Besides,
you're better off not knowing.

364
00:37:33,173 --> 00:37:37,485
The people 's candidate, Senator
Vernon Trent, promises no new taxes.

365
00:37:37,813 --> 00:37:40,373
And you can take that to the bank!

366
00:37:44,053 --> 00:37:47,045
What'll I do with this guy?
I want to help him. . .

367
00:37:47,253 --> 00:37:51,007
. . .but he's all over TV.
He's a crooked cop involved in--

368
00:37:54,493 --> 00:37:56,131
Why are you out of bed?

369
00:37:56,373 --> 00:37:57,522
I've got you.

370
00:37:57,933 --> 00:37:59,525
Police speculate that Storm...

371
00:37:59,733 --> 00:38:03,772
... who is known to have ties
with criminal elements...

372
00:38:04,053 --> 00:38:06,772
...could have involved
his contacts in his escape.

373
00:38:07,093 --> 00:38:10,290
Storm was thought to have been
a murder victim. A casualty...

374
00:38:10,653 --> 00:38:13,372
...of his own greed.
A widespread search is now being--

375
00:38:18,333 --> 00:38:21,723
This is Mason Storm. I'd like
to speak with Jerry Dunphy.

376
00:38:24,373 --> 00:38:26,648
No, it's not a joke.

377
00:38:29,453 --> 00:38:32,684
We can't stay here.
They'll trace us from the hospital.

378
00:38:33,053 --> 00:38:36,409
Nobody knows I'm here.
I'm housesitting.

379
00:38:36,733 --> 00:38:39,452
It belongs to a friend of my parents.

380
00:38:39,773 --> 00:38:42,333
He's in China on research for 6 months.

381
00:38:43,253 --> 00:38:45,767
The medical center
only has my apartment address.

382
00:38:46,013 --> 00:38:48,925
Not even my friends have this number.

383
00:38:50,053 --> 00:38:52,169
You've got to believe me.

384
00:38:52,413 --> 00:38:54,563
You're safe here, okay?

385
00:38:57,533 --> 00:39:01,492
This reporter was contacted personally
by the infamous "Coma Cop"...

386
00:39:01,733 --> 00:39:03,371
...fugitive officer Mason Storm...

387
00:39:03,613 --> 00:39:06,571
... who, until days ago,
had been in a 7-year coma.

388
00:39:06,933 --> 00:39:11,404
Storm said he's innocent of charges
made against him in the press...

389
00:39:11,653 --> 00:39:14,167
...and that he has
indisputable proof of this.

390
00:39:14,453 --> 00:39:17,968
He has promised me a first look
at his alleged proof.

391
00:39:19,413 --> 00:39:22,803
I want 24-hour surveillance
on that son of a bitch. . .

392
00:39:23,053 --> 00:39:25,362
. . .and those 2 nurses from the hospital.

393
00:39:35,293 --> 00:39:37,602
No, I can do it myself.

394
00:39:38,013 --> 00:39:39,605
You do it then.

395
00:39:49,213 --> 00:39:50,965
You give me this beard?

396
00:40:01,373 --> 00:40:02,442
You tried.

397
00:40:12,373 --> 00:40:15,570
-You ever been to Chinatown?
-Yeah. Why?

398
00:40:17,293 --> 00:40:21,571
This is a list of herbs and needles
that I need for my recovery.

399
00:40:21,853 --> 00:40:24,083
Where did you learn to write Chinese?

400
00:40:25,573 --> 00:40:30,363
When I was a kid, my dad was a
missionary. I was raised in the Orient.

401
00:40:30,973 --> 00:40:32,884
As a young white boy over there. . .

402
00:40:33,093 --> 00:40:36,563
. . .I needed to learn how to fight,
as you can imagine.

403
00:40:36,893 --> 00:40:37,962
I remember. . .

404
00:40:38,453 --> 00:40:41,172
. . .my first martial arts teacher
said to me:

405
00:40:41,573 --> 00:40:43,803
"So why do you come to me?"

406
00:40:44,613 --> 00:40:46,604
I say,
"To learn how to fight. "

407
00:40:46,813 --> 00:40:49,566
And he says,
"So you want to hurt people.

408
00:40:50,533 --> 00:40:53,172
But do you want to be great?"
I say, "Yeah.

409
00:40:54,133 --> 00:40:55,964
I want to be great. "

410
00:40:56,613 --> 00:41:01,482
He says, "Then first learn how
to heal people to be great.

411
00:41:01,893 --> 00:41:04,202
To hurt people is easy. "

412
00:41:24,573 --> 00:41:27,087
Look at you!
You look great.

413
00:41:27,293 --> 00:41:28,408
Like it?

414
00:41:40,773 --> 00:41:43,241
That's enough.
Why don't you go sit down?

415
00:41:52,853 --> 00:41:54,366
That bad?

416
00:41:57,693 --> 00:42:00,571
If you need me,
I'll be in the outer room.

417
00:44:33,853 --> 00:44:35,889
O'Malley's the key.
We must find him.

418
00:44:36,093 --> 00:44:40,211
You can't compare blood pressure
now with when you're in a coma.

419
00:44:40,413 --> 00:44:42,688
What's this?
555 over four digits.

420
00:44:42,893 --> 00:44:44,884
That's crazy.
Let me see that.

421
00:44:45,733 --> 00:44:48,930
Martha's chicken scratches.
She probably can't even read them.

422
00:44:49,173 --> 00:44:50,765
You know what it is?

423
00:44:51,093 --> 00:44:52,765
It's a phone number.

424
00:45:18,253 --> 00:45:22,565
When you phoned I asked
everyone here at the home. . .

425
00:45:22,853 --> 00:45:27,165
. . .and there is no O'Malley here.
But it is possible. . .

426
00:45:27,653 --> 00:45:30,645
. . .O'Malley is a relation
of someone here.

427
00:45:31,133 --> 00:45:36,048
Why not leave me your number and
I'll call you if there's any contact.

428
00:45:37,533 --> 00:45:38,852
Can I phone you?

429
00:45:39,933 --> 00:45:41,571
Of course, my dear.

430
00:45:42,973 --> 00:45:45,771
-Here, let me do that.
-That's all right.

431
00:46:10,853 --> 00:46:12,571
You old devil!

432
00:46:37,533 --> 00:46:39,364
Mason Storm.

433
00:47:44,573 --> 00:47:46,450
Hi. I'm sorry.

434
00:47:47,653 --> 00:47:49,848
I don't mean to interrupt.

435
00:47:50,973 --> 00:47:53,441
I was just passing by and I thought. . .

436
00:47:55,253 --> 00:47:57,005
. . .you might like a flower.

437
00:48:53,173 --> 00:48:54,925
I like that.

438
00:49:53,853 --> 00:49:56,526
Now I lay me down to sleep....

439
00:49:58,213 --> 00:50:00,363
Now we say it together, okay?

440
00:50:00,613 --> 00:50:03,286
I pray the Lord my soul to keep.

441
00:50:03,773 --> 00:50:05,968
If I die before I wake...

442
00:50:06,173 --> 00:50:08,926
...l pray the Lord my soul to take.

443
00:50:19,453 --> 00:50:22,172
This is Martha Coe.
I can 't come to the phone--

444
00:50:22,373 --> 00:50:24,762
Pick up, Martha.
Please pick up!

445
00:50:26,213 --> 00:50:28,124
Are you there?
I'm coming over.

446
00:50:45,853 --> 00:50:47,923
Are you there?
I'm coming over.

447
00:50:48,613 --> 00:50:50,365
You called it right, Axel.

448
00:50:51,173 --> 00:50:52,925
Our girlfriend just showed up.

449
00:51:10,693 --> 00:51:13,161
Martha, open up.
It's me.

450
00:51:16,973 --> 00:51:18,406
What's up?

451
00:51:20,773 --> 00:51:21,842
Looking for Martha?

452
00:51:22,373 --> 00:51:23,726
You know where she is?

453
00:51:26,333 --> 00:51:28,369
You haven't seen the news?

454
00:51:29,733 --> 00:51:31,132
She's dead.

455
00:51:32,413 --> 00:51:34,973
She was strangled over in Westwood.

456
00:51:36,453 --> 00:51:37,363
Know something?

457
00:51:38,453 --> 00:51:40,808
You look like the bitch
whose picture's on TV.

458
00:51:43,813 --> 00:51:46,168
The one whose house they found her at.

459
00:51:46,493 --> 00:51:48,768
Hey, get over here!

460
00:51:52,653 --> 00:51:54,371
Okay, boys, mount up.

461
00:52:12,973 --> 00:52:15,931
Ernie, you forgot my buttermilk!

462
00:52:16,253 --> 00:52:17,368
Shit!

463
00:52:45,053 --> 00:52:46,566
O'Malley.

464
00:53:03,693 --> 00:53:05,604
That's Sonny, all right.

465
00:53:06,693 --> 00:53:08,092
The kid's a track star.

466
00:53:08,293 --> 00:53:10,568
He does the hundred in 1 1 flat.

467
00:53:10,933 --> 00:53:14,084
He's going to be real fast,
like his old man was.

468
00:53:14,373 --> 00:53:15,772
What do you mean "was"?

469
00:53:16,653 --> 00:53:18,371
I'm not over the hill.

470
00:53:19,013 --> 00:53:20,651
At least, I hope not.

471
00:53:22,053 --> 00:53:23,964
How'd you pull this off?

472
00:53:24,973 --> 00:53:27,328
He made it to my house
the night you were shot.

473
00:53:28,133 --> 00:53:31,569
I got him hidden, played it out
like he was dead. . .

474
00:53:31,853 --> 00:53:34,083
. . .staged his funeral
with yours and Felicia's.

475
00:53:34,573 --> 00:53:36,370
Everybody bought it.

476
00:53:39,293 --> 00:53:41,682
Where is he?
ls he safe?

477
00:53:42,173 --> 00:53:45,927
Ventura Trinity Prep School,
under my mother's maiden name, Wade.

478
00:53:46,533 --> 00:53:49,127
No one has any idea that he's your son.

479
00:53:49,373 --> 00:53:51,443
So that was your mother that Andy found.

480
00:53:51,893 --> 00:53:56,205
Your nurse friend? Yeah.
She left a number and I traced you here.

481
00:54:02,013 --> 00:54:04,163
I don't know how to thank you.

482
00:54:04,733 --> 00:54:06,371
I have no words.

483
00:54:07,653 --> 00:54:10,167
Just seeing your ugly ass alive
is enough for me.

484
00:54:22,813 --> 00:54:24,769
That night in the hospital. . .

485
00:54:26,173 --> 00:54:28,562
. . .I found the audio tape in your vest.

486
00:54:29,373 --> 00:54:31,933
I must've played that tape 1 000 times. . .

487
00:54:32,213 --> 00:54:36,604
. . .Iooking for little quirks
in the voices, phrases that repeat.

488
00:54:36,893 --> 00:54:37,882
Nada.

489
00:54:38,133 --> 00:54:39,646
Where is the tape?

490
00:54:39,893 --> 00:54:41,963
-I turned it in for evidence.
-What?

491
00:54:42,173 --> 00:54:43,572
Don't worry, I made a dupe.

492
00:54:43,893 --> 00:54:46,691
Meanwhile, I thought you'd
take some pleasure in this.

493
00:54:48,853 --> 00:54:50,764
And there's more in the car.

494
00:54:51,933 --> 00:54:53,969
You were not wrong, my friend.

495
00:54:55,293 --> 00:54:56,965
You were not wrong.

496
00:55:05,373 --> 00:55:07,364
What's happened to you?

497
00:55:18,333 --> 00:55:20,972
I was on the case
maybe a year and a half. . .

498
00:55:21,173 --> 00:55:23,562
. . .trying to find out
who pulled the trigger.

499
00:55:24,773 --> 00:55:26,809
But it was like swimming through shit.

500
00:55:27,013 --> 00:55:31,564
Everywhere I turned,
people told me to back off, get lost.

501
00:55:32,333 --> 00:55:34,244
Then one morning the phone rings.

502
00:55:34,533 --> 00:55:36,444
Immaculate Heart Emergency.

503
00:55:37,733 --> 00:55:39,963
Someone ran my mother off the road.

504
00:55:40,293 --> 00:55:42,966
Her back's broken.
She's paralyzed.

505
00:55:44,213 --> 00:55:46,363
I'm sorry, O'Mal.

506
00:55:48,493 --> 00:55:53,408
That night, there's a note in my locker
telling me it's no accident.

507
00:55:54,453 --> 00:55:56,045
What the hell could I do?

508
00:55:56,293 --> 00:56:00,172
I've got my hands tied behind
my back. I can't wave or salute.

509
00:56:01,293 --> 00:56:03,568
So I put my papers in.

510
00:56:04,613 --> 00:56:06,763
Took a 3/4 pension.

511
00:56:07,733 --> 00:56:10,167
You know me,
I never would have backed off.

512
00:56:10,693 --> 00:56:14,402
